In this speech, President Trump addresses military spouses and recognizes their heroic service. He acknowledges the sacrifices they make, including enduring long separations during deployments and moving their families frequently. The President highlights the importance of military spouses in maintaining morale and supporting the military community. He also mentions the recent approval of a $700 billion budget for the military, which includes raises for the military personnel. Furthermore, President Trump discusses the administration's commitment to expand employment opportunities for military spouses, aiming to reduce the high unemployment rate among them. He mentions taking executive action to promote military spouse hiring across the federal government and encourages American businesses to provide job opportunities for military spouses. The President expresses gratitude to military spouses for their devotion to the nation and concludes by signing an executive order to support their career pursuits.